This paper is about multi-task reinforcement learning, which involves training an agent to perform well on multiple related tasks. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and computer vision (cs.CV). Given that the paper proposes a new algorithm for multi-task reinforcement learning that involves learning a dynamical model, it is most likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). However, given the potential applications of this work in robotics and control, it is also possible that it could be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, given that the paper evaluates its approach on continuous control benchmarks, it is also possible that it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision), which often involves tasks related to image or video analysis.
